<paragraph blockId="14.[151,736,1758,1785]" box="[151,736,1758,1785]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,736,1758,1785]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Stejneger, 1904" authorityName="Stejneger" authorityYear="1904" box="[151,736,1758,1785]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grandisquamis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,736,1758,1785]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,538,1758,1785]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Sphaerodactylus grandisquamis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Stejneger, L." box="[546,736,1758,1784]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" pagination="549 - 724" refId="ref23174" refString="Stejneger, L. (1904) Herpetology of Porto Rico. Report of the United States National Museum, 1902, 549 - 724. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11835" type="journal article" year="1904">Stejneger, 1904</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1830,2037]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1436,153,395]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="166" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">
All populations of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1859" box="[402,552,1830,1856]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrolepis">
<emphasis box="[402,552,1830,1856]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">S. macrolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex occurring on 
<collectingCountry box="[811,943,1830,1857]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
and its satellite islands (e.g. Piñeros) are restricted to this taxon. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stejneger" authorityYear="1904" box="[392,586,1866,1892]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grandisquamis">
<emphasis box="[392,586,1866,1892]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">S. grandisquamis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described by Stegneger (1904) and was reaffirmed as a valid taxon by 
<bibRefCitation author="Grant, C." box="[254,411,1902,1928]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" pagination="37 - 39" refId="ref19026" refString="Grant, C. (1932 c) The herpetology of Vieques Island. Journal of the Department of Agriculture of Porto Rico, 16, 37 - 39." type="journal article" year="1932">Grant (1932c)</bibRefCitation>
but referred to as a subspecies of 
<emphasis box="[785,974,1902,1928]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1859" box="[785,935,1902,1928]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrolepis">S. macrolepis</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[942,974,1902,1928]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" sensu="lato">s.l.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, R. &amp; Schwartz, A." box="[1015,1327,1902,1929]" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" pagination="193 - 260" refId="ref23344" refString="Thomas, R. &amp; Schwartz, A. (1966) Sphaerodactylus (Gekkonidae) in the greater Puerto Rico region. Bulletin of the Florida State Museum, Biological Sciences, 10, 193 - 260." type="journal article" year="1966">Thomas &amp; Schwartz (1966)</bibRefCitation>
. This taxon may include several undescribed species and in this paper we keep most of the subspecific names from 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, R. &amp; Schwartz, A." pageId="14" pageNumber="165" pagination="193 - 260" refId="ref23344" refString="Thomas, R. &amp; Schwartz, A. (1966) Sphaerodactylus (Gekkonidae) in the greater Puerto Rico region. Bulletin of the Florida State Museum, Biological Sciences, 10, 193 - 260." type="journal article" year="1966">Thomas &amp; Schwartz (1966)</bibRefCitation>
. Additional study is needed to better resolve the relationships among these subspecies, but at the moment we highlight the monophyly of this taxon, which is comprised of the subspecies: 
<emphasis box="[1152,1374,2010,2036]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">
S. g. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stejneger" authorityYear="1904" box="[1208,1374,2010,2036]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="14" pageNumber="165" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grandisquamis">grandisquamis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="166" pageId="14" pageNumber="165">S. g. guarionex, S. g. ateles</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[417,567,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">S. g. mimetes</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[582,726,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">S. g. spanius</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Stejneger, 1904" authorityName="Stejneger" authorityYear="1904" box="[788,936,153,179]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stibarus">
<emphasis box="[788,936,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">S. g. stibarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[953,1115,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">S. g. phoberus</emphasis>
was not supported by either molecular [this study] or morphological data [
<bibRefCitation author="Padilla, L. F." box="[665,818,188,215]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" refId="ref21580" refString="Padilla, L. F. (2006) Geographic variation in color pattern on Sphaerodactylus macrolepis Gunther 1859, (Sauria: Gekkonidae). M. Sc. Thesis, University of Puerto Rico, San Juan. 153 pp." type="book" year="2006">Padilla, 2006</bibRefCitation>
] and is thus synonomized with 
<emphasis box="[1171,1393,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">
S. g. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stejneger" authorityYear="1904" box="[1227,1393,189,215]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grandisquamis">grandisquamis</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="166" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,153,395]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,777,224,251]" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">
General traits of 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[401,777,224,251]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stejneger" authorityYear="1904" box="[401,773,224,251]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grandisquamis">Sphaerodactylus grandisquamis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</emphasis>
Compared to other members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gunther" authorityYear="1859" box="[1176,1326,225,251]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="macrolepis">
<emphasis box="[1176,1326,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">S. macrolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stejneger" authorityYear="1904" box="[151,344,261,287]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grandisquamis">
<emphasis box="[151,344,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">S. grandisquamis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
males have a higher number of escutcheon scales (67–95); males with dorsal stippled lines (except in 
<emphasis box="[179,326,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">S. g. mimetes</emphasis>
); males exhibit a cephalic figure; males have a light line behind the eye; females with dorsal medial lines separated (except in 
<taxonomicName box="[439,556,333,359]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stibarus">
<emphasis box="[439,556,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">S. stibarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
where it forms a blotch or imperfect line); and a long and narrow snout (except in 
<taxonomicName box="[180,298,369,395]" class="Reptilia" family="Sphaerodactylidae" genus="Sphaerodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="15" pageNumber="166" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stibarus">
<emphasis box="[180,298,369,395]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="166">S. stibarus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
